Finding the right salvage car website depends on whether you are an individual looking for a project or a licensed dealer. The top industry platforms offer massive inventories, with heavy hitters like Copart and IAA acting as the primary sources for most salvage and insurance vehicles.The top 10 car salvage and repairable vehicle websites are categorized below based on accessibility and inventory type:Public-Access Platforms (No Dealer License Usually Required)Copart: The global leader in online salvage car auctions. It allows both individuals and dealers to bid on a massive inventory of wrecked, repairable, and stolen-recovered vehicles.IAA (Insurance Auto Auctions): One of the largest platforms for insurance write-offs, total losses, and fleet vehicles. It features detailed condition reports and accepts public buyers in many states.SalvageBid: A licensed broker that allows public buyers to participate in major dealer-only auto auctions without needing a state dealer license.A Better Bid: An auto auction platform connected directly to Copart's inventory, offering an easy-to-use bidding interface for the public.eRepairables: Aggregates damaged and salvage-title listings from various auto recyclers, insurance auctions, and third-party sellers into one searchable directory.RideSafely: Specializes in salvaging and auctioning cars, motorcycles, and trucks to the general public with no dealer license required.Auction Aggregators & AlternativesAuto Auction Mall: Provides public users access to dealer-exclusive wholesale and salvage auto auctions, with agents available to help facilitate the bidding process.Dashub: A marketplace that helps retail buyers purchase directly from salvage and wholesale auto auctions without a dealer's license.eBay Motors: A highly accessible marketplace where private sellers, salvage yards, and dealers list repairable cars, parts cars, and project vehicles.Purple Wave: Primarily an equipment and vehicle auction site, but they regularly auction off wrecked, seized, and salvage vehicles with no buyer reserves.Are you looking for a specific make and model, or are you trying to buy a vehicle specifically to rebuild and title for the road?

