What Are Car Auction Sites?
Online Car Auction With Blue SUV

Car auction sites are online marketplaces where individuals, dealerships, and wholesalers can bid on, buy, or sell vehicles in real time. These platforms act as a digital alternative to traditional dealerships, offering everything from everyday used cars to luxury, classic, and salvage vehicles.

Unlike in-person auctions, everything happens online. Buyers can compare listings, review vehicle history, and place bids from anywhere. Sellers, on the other hand, gain access to a much larger audience, helping them sell vehicles faster and often at competitive prices.

Best Car Auction Sites of 2026
The automotive market continues to evolve, making auto auction sites more popular than ever. While many platforms appear similar, each offers unique features and advantages. Below are the best car auction websites to consider this year.

eBay Motors
eBay Motors Vehicle Parts And Accessories

eBay Motors remains one of the most widely used car auction websites. It offers everything from used vehicles to parts and accessories, making it ideal for both casual buyers and collectors. Also, it caters to private sellers and automotive dealerships. It has an extensive selection and a user-friendly bidding system that facilitates auto auction buyers to bid on vehicles or “Buy It Now” for faster transactions.

Pros
Extensive inventory of used and new vehicles and specialty and classic cars.
Smooth integration with the traditional eBay platform, allowing registered users to access eBay Motors easily.
The choice between bidding or instant buying options.
eBay provides purchase protection for added security.
No auction fee for bidding cars online.
Parts and accessories are offered to maintain or update vehicles.
Cons
Shipping is not included; buyers are responsible for arranging transportation.
eBay charges seller fees, which may impact final costs.
Limited exclusive deals in comparison to other auction sites online.
Finding a “great deal” is challenging due to competitive bidding, which results in higher final prices.
eBay Motors is a trusted platform for car auctions with a vast selection. For transportation, you can opt for Sherpa Auto Transport. For luxury cars, it’s recommended to opt for enclosed auto transport.

Copart
Copart Online Auto Auctions Homepage

Copart is one of the leading auto auction sites specializing in salvage and clean title vehicles. It’s popular among rebuilders and budget-conscious buyers. It includes insurance companies, rental agencies and car dealerships.

Moreover, it has an extensive inventory and user-friendly features to facilitate buyers, including individual buyers (DIY enthusiasts), professional automotive businesses, and rebuilders. It’s ideal for those seeking budget-friendly options.

Pros
Affordable salvage vehicles at low prices.
Extensive inventory, including salvage and clean title vehicles.
Caters to individual buyers as well as automotive businesses.
User-friendly car bidding sites with advanced search filters, helping buyers find the ideal vehicle.
Offers several online car bidding options, including proxy bidding, for added convenience.
Cons
Vehicles are often sold as-is, with limited inspections leading to uncertainties and additional repair costs.
Copart charges various fees that can add up quickly.
Requires a membership fee, which may not suit occasional buyers.
Copart is ideal for those seeking damaged cars for parts or restoration. For shipping solutions, check out Sherpa Auto Transport’s guide on damaged car transport.

IAAI (Insurance Auto Auctions)
IAAI Insurance Auto Auctions Vehicle Sales

IAAI specializes in auctioning off insurance-salvage vehicles, providing access to a range of damaged, repairable, and parts-only vehicles at a discount. It includes vehicles with minor to severe damage and also covers flooded cars. IAAI gives buyers the opportunity to find vehicles at lower prices for various purposes, such as repair, parts harvesting, or resale.

Pros
A large inventory of vehicles, including salvaged, damaged, and flood-damaged cars, allows for a broader selection.
Inventory includes vehicles from insurance claims.
Ideal for buyers interested in budget-friendly options.
User-friendly web interface with advanced search filters to help narrow down the ideal vehicle.
Online and proxy bidding are available for those who cannot attend the in-person auction.
Cons
Vehicles that are sold “as-is,” often limit warranties, which may result in higher repair costs.
It is not ideal for buyers seeking vehicles in perfect condition or with minimal damage.
However, IAAI is perfect for budget-conscious buyers looking for repairable vehicles. Sherpa Auto Transport can help deliver your purchase safely.

Adesa
Adesa Transparent Digital Auto Auction Platform

Adesa is one of the largest online car auction sites. It primarily serves licensed dealers but also offers limited access to the general public through certain channels. It is known for its extensive network of physical auction locations and online bidding platform. However, individual buyers may not find it ideal due to its primary focus on business-to-business transactions and limited consumer protection policies.

Pros
Multiple auction locations across North America for both in-person and online bidding.
Vehicles typically undergo inspections, providing buyers with detailed condition reports.
Diverse inventory of vehicles catering to various business needs.
User-friendly online car auction websites with advanced search features to facilitate buyers.
Different bidding options available that include online and proxy bidding for cars.
Cons
Primarily designed for licensed dealers, limiting direct access for individual buyers.
A membership fee is attached along with  additional fees for certain services.
Limited consumer protection policies due to the business-to-business nature of this car online auction platform.
Thanks to its vast network and thorough inspections, Adesa is ideal for professional buyers or those with access to dealer licenses. Sherpa Auto Transport can help transport your vehicle if you purchase through Adesa’s dealer auctions.

Auto Auction Mall
Dealer Only Auto Auction Access Portal

Auto Auction Mall bridges the gap between public buyers and dealer-only auctions, making it one of the best online car auction sites for individuals. It lets them bid on cars that are not easily accessible, enabling them to purchase vehicles at wholesale prices.

This auto auction online platform offers a wide range of vehicles, from used cars to salvage titles. Moreover, it provides support throughout the buying process.

Pros
Offers access to dealer-only auctions for individuals, extending options for regular buyers so that they can purchase vehicles at wholesale prices.
Thousands of vehicles are available across multiple categories.
Offers a user-friendly car auction website with advanced search features and filters to help buyers find the perfect vehicle.
Provides consistent customer support throughout the buying process.
Cons
Most vehicles are sold as-is with limited condition information, so buyers should inspect reports carefully.
Buyers may face competition from dealers and other professionals during the cheap car auction process.
 Service fees and shipping arrangements are the buyer’s responsibility.
The potential risk associated with purchasing salvage or damaged vehicles may require significant repair work.
Auto Auction Mall is an excellent choice for those wanting dealer-level access without a license. Sherpa Auto Transport can ensure safe delivery of your auction purchase, providing peace of mind from auction to driveway.
